1 olive oil
1 bag baby broccoli
1 leek
½ lemon
1 packet pork loin steaks
1 packet Cherry Sauce
1 packet mashed potato
1 packet walnuts
1 g parsley
1 sachet All-American Spice Blend

• Trim baby broccoli. Thinly slice white and light green parts of leek. Cut lemon into wedges
• Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a frying pan over medium-high heat. Cook veggies, until tender, 4-5 mins
• Add a squeeze of lemon juice. Toss and season. Transfer to a bowl

• Return frying pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil
• Cook pork until cooked through, 3-4 mins each side
• In last minute of cook time, add spice blend and a splash of water. Turn to coat
• Add cherry glaze and turn to coat

• Meanwhile, transfer mashed potato to a bowl. Microwave until hot and steaming, 3 mins. Season to taste
• Plate up pork, greens and mash
• Top with walnuts. Tear over parsley. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges.